[[span class="st"]]FOREWORD:[[/span]] I've been with the Foundation long enough to recognize when I'm only begrudgingly consulted, and that's what's happening here. Despite the fact that I am the world's premier expert on the present subject, despite my possession of firsthand knowledge regarding the disaster which rendered it supposedly indescribable, and despite my persistent entreaties to be looped into the research and containment process, I have been stonewalled at every turn until the utmost end of alternative resources.

I, Dr. Dougall Alton Deering, once stood at the head of a scientific project second in importance to none on this Earth. We faced an Anomalous waste crisis of unprecedented and ever-escalating scale, and my staff and I were charged with its amelioration. Here is my precise, cogent, one hundred percent accurate explanation of how that worked -- and what, through no fault of my own, went wrong with it.

----

[[span class="st"]]DESCRIPTION:[[/span]] [[span class="diss"]]Site-43 is the designation for a facility constructed one kilometre beneath Ipperwash Provincial Park in Lambton County,[[/span]] Ontario, Canada [[span class="diss"]]for research and containment operations, the most vital of which was the advancement of Acroamatic Abatement: neutralization of esoteric effluence. Site-43 contained four of the most advanced AcroAbate facilities on Earth, though there existed[[/span]] multiple satellite facilities [[span class="diss"]]at other Sites and Areas internationally. Our tireless efforts resulted in a stalemate with this implacable opponent, until in a moment of personal inspiration I was able to devise a novel abatement method which could permanently terminate the matter in question via the application of advanced parascience.[[/span]]

[[span class="diss"]]I enlisted the aid of Chief Amelia Torosyan-Deering to construct a device we termed the DePLExA Engine, after consultation with various external experts (including Dr. Ilse Reynders and Dr. Placeholder McDoctorate). The device eventuated[[/span]] my [[span class="diss"]]prime[[/span]] aspiration [[span class="diss"]]for Anomalous waste: that it be conceptually[[/span]] erased [[span class="diss"]]from existence, as though it had never existed in the first place. Effluence went into the engine,[[/span]] and nothing came out, [[span class="diss"]]and retrocausally nothing went in,[[/span]] resulting in [[span class="diss"]]a paradox that powered the machine itself. It was elegant, flawless, and effective. We had beaten back the beast. We had ended the[[/span]] crisis.

[[span class="diss"]]My shortsighted consultants -- or if not shortsighted, then actively malicious -- caused the device to be deactivated at a[[/span]] critical [[span class="diss"]]moment. This allowed the original course of causality to retroactively resume, and we experienced a total effluence maximalization effect unabated by any other mechanisms, which in short[[/span]] order [[span class="diss"]]caused Site-43 and Nexus-94 within which it is situated to be[[/span]] stricken [[span class="diss"]]from consensus reality.[[/span]]

[[span class="diss"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering and I witnessed these events.[[/span]] I attempted [[span class="diss"]]to escape with her in order to help coordinate disaster mitigation and relief efforts, but Dr. Reynders interfered in[[/span]] a selfish bid [[span class="diss"]]to preserve her own existence and we were instead transported from the facility together.[[/span]]

[[span class="diss"]]The conceptually[[/span]] null [[span class="diss"]]space you call Nexus-7243 is Site-43 and Nexus-94. They still exist. And it[[/span]] is my duty [[span class="diss"]]to restore them.[[/span]]

Unlike my colleagues, I do NOT shirk my responsibilities.
