[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I don't think--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You think too much, actually, but never about the right things. You think about how unfair it is, you think about how it's not your fault, but you never examine your motivations. Your job, doctor, is to resolve the abatement crisis. You've only been pretending to do that. The world's //fucking// toilets are overflowing, and here you are plunging down your back-clog of guilt on our borrowed time.

