[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You didn't. Tell me you didn't.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] We ran a month of simulations on pocket dimension dumping. The consensus was that without full timeline coherence, the transfer process would almost certainly collapse the destination, rubberbanding just like when DePLExA--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You lied to me.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] It's just a detail! Not even a major detail. In every respect except for ontological strength factor--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] We've been dumping hot garbage on our neighbours. MAGIC DRAWER hasn't been selecting from the set of stable pockets, it's been selecting from the set of stable //timelines.//

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] I wanted to tell you.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] //I// wanted to tell you! But I knew--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You knew I'd never...

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering sits down.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] That wasn't it. You didn't need my help.

= //<Dr. Deering approaches her. He takes her hands. She does not look up at him.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] That isn't true. I needed you on my side. I needed you so I could make this possible. For--

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering shoves him away.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Don't say it.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Amelia--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You wanted me to think you'd found a permanent solution. Like you promised. You really are a sad sack of shit, Dougall Deering.

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering laughs, leans forward and holds her head in her hands.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] So, it's targeting us. Fine. What do we do about that?

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering suddenly stands up.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] No, actually, I need more information. Where precisely have we been sending these packets? What specific physical locations?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Site-43. Always Site-43.

= //<Silence on recording.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] There is no Site-43.

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] You'll recall the chronological--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Oh, for... the chronological calculations. You said time was variable in the pocket dimensions. We've been sending this stuff back in time, too? Into other people's pasts?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] It's a factor of transfer dilation, opportunity windows, the ratchet principle--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Where in our past is this packet going?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] MAGIC DRAWER selects whatever the most...

= //<Dr. Deering sits down on the edge of the nearest chair. He almost falls off, clutching at the associated console for stability. Chief Torosyan-Deering moves as if to support him, then pulls back.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What? What's wrong?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] It can't.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What can't?

= //<Dr. Reynders gasps.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What? Doug, what's wrong?

= //<Dr. Deering stands up abruptly. The chair spins away across the aisle.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] No! No. We're not doing this.

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] It's already been done. The past is a pact, Dougall. 

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] No.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Wait.

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] We need to send something Anomalous through the aperture, and we need to do it soon. We can't destabilize the cosmos for this.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] //<muttering>// You think this is the cosmos being //stable?//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] WAIT.

= //<Silence on recording.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I won't do it, Amelia. I didn't...

= //<Dr. Deering sags.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I didn't do it. It wasn't //me.//

----

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering convenes the primary operational staff of Area-21 to review the data from MAGIC DRAWER and determine whether the executive interpretation of the packet delivery target site is correct. It is unanimously agreed that the device is preparing to transport esoteric effluence to Acroamatic Abatement Facility AAF-D on 8 September, 2028.>//

----

= //<The executive staff have reconvened in the operations control room.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]]  This isn't a problem. It's an opportunity! We can... we can send something innocuous. Enough to get the job done, but not enough to kill him.

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] Amelia...

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]]  No, just listen to me, okay? Okay?

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] Okay, but we can't do it.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]]  Why not? //Why not?// We just discovered that Phil was never meant to die in the first place! //We caused it.// We can un-cause it! We can fix the whole thing, and all we have to do is whiff the next shot.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] You're saying //I// caused it.

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] We, these versions of ourselves, everything we've done -- with widespread multiversal consequences! -- are the products of Philip Deering's death. We can't create a toxic uber-paradox to save one human life.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]]  We're meant to fix this! It's a one in a million... no, an //indescribably unlikely// coincidence that we'd end up targeting ourselves. What could explain that, outside of fate?

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] Every target is indescribably unlikely, particularly from the perspective of each.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] She's right, Ilse. There's just no way we're the next recipient on blind luck. It would be the single greatest probabilistic outlier ever recorded. Even //theorized.//

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] Yes. It's infinitely more likely that something went wrong with the machine, and it failed to model the timeplane curve correctly; theoretically, we should be the 'end' of the arc.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] More mistakes.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] No. Don't even.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I wasn't--

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Don't say it! I'm telling you, //this wasn't me.// Place did the calculations. We need to call him.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Place? Are you serious?

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] I've been trying, Dougall. He's gone silent. //Again.//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Fuck! //FUCK!// How long do we have?

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Two hours and change. Long enough to debate the solution.

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] There's nothing to debate.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] There is. Ilse, Doug, we //can// save him. 

= //<She takes Dr. Deering's shoulders in her hands.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] We work miracles every day. If you burned the braincells in this room, you could power Toronto for a lifetime. 

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] No.

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering turns her head to face Dr. Reynders.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I crawled my way out of Hell for this chance. To do right by someone I love. Tell me you don't understand that, //Ilse,// and remember why I was there in the first place.

= //<Dr. Reynders opens her mouth, then looks away and does not respond. Chief Torosyan-Deering turns back to Dr. Deering.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] We can bring him back.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Maybe...

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Yes. You know it's right. It makes //sense.//

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] We can't.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] We //can.// We can start over!

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] AMELIA!

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I NEED MY HUSBAND BACK!

= //<Silence on recording.>//

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering releases Dr. Deering's shoulders.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I'm sorry, Doug.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] It's okay.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I'm so sorry.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] It's okay. I knew, of course.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I... look, I didn't...

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] I can't spare you two a moment. You know that. We're out of time to waste. We need to decide how we're going to handle this.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] We...

= //<Silence on recording.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] We need to let him go.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] That's only part of it.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] //You// need to let him go. //I// need to take responsibility.

----

= //<Dr. Deering calls a recess to allow the Historioglyphics Division to compare the next packet with the reported contents of Acroamatic Abatement Facility AAF-D on 8 September 2028. Chief Torosyan-Deering and Dr. Reynders are engaged in conversation within the former's office when they are alerted to the powerup of MAGIC DRAWER by a momentary power fluctuation. They return to the operations control room to find Dr. Deering absent; a brief search locates him within the maintenance access corridor to the device's delivery aperture. Chief Torosyan-Deering rushes to the outer door, finding it locked, while Dr. Reynders remains in operations control.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What are you doing?

= //<She hammers on the door. Dr. Deering is visible beyond the porthole, standing in the empty aperture, clenching and unclenching his hands.>//

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering activates a panel beside the door.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You're standing next to the loading chamber. It's not going to fire until you close the inner door.

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering attempts to open the outer door. Her access code is denied.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What are you DOING?

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering hammers on the door.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I know you can hear me. Dougall!

= //<Dr. Reynders speaks via P. A. system.>//

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] He's overriding the safeties.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Why?

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] He's going to--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] No. Absolutely not.

= //<She hammers on the porthole, breaking the skin on her right hand in the process.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] DOUGALL! What the fuck are you--

= //<The overhead lights flicker, and a persistent hum is heard throughout Area-21. MAGIC DRAWER is preparing to deliver its packet.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Stop! Stop! We can work this out. Talk to me, or I swear on his memory I'm going to shut the whole system down.

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] You can't do that.

= //<Dr. Deering turns to face Chief Torosyan-Deering.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] You can't do that.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Watch me.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] We don't mean you //can't// do that, really. We're saying it's the wrong move. Amelia, I'm sorry. I thought this would be easier if you and I didn't... didn't talk again.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You always want to do it the easy way.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I'm making up for it now.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You say that, but from where I'm standing, you're about to give up and leave us to fix the mess you made. How is that not the easy way out?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I know what killed Phil.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You've always known what killed Phil. And so have I.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Exactly.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I killed Phil. 

= //<Dr. Deering taps his chest.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] //I// killed Phil. And this is how I did it.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Come out here, and let's discuss.

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] The ramifications of what you're suggesting--

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I'm not suggesting anything. This is what happened. The thing that coiled around him did so for a reason. It ignored me. It went for him. It solved the problem.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Solved the...?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] That's why I'm the only one who could see it, at first. //It was me.//

= //<Dr. Deering spreads his hands wide.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I'm the loop.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] That doesn't... 

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] This packet is one hundred percent paraspectral. It's the extra material that showed up after Phil flushed AAF-D, the stuff nobody could account for. It's the source of the thing that took his life. And that thing behaved with //purpose,// Amelia.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] That doesn't mean you have to...

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] It does, though. The loop is stable, so long as we get this next part right. Otherwise...

= //<Dr. Deering looks up at the ceiling of the chamber.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] //Paradox//, Ilse.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What's he talking about?

= //<Dr. Reynders hesitates for a moment, then speaks.>//

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] Phil dying set all of this in motion, and it's cross-multiversal now. Phil has to die again. He always has to die. And it has to be a sure thing.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Meaning we need control at the moment of crisis. What we send needs to have //agency.// And a shot of undifferentiated ectoplasm hasn't got that.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What makes you think you won't just melt into nothing when the packet pours in on you?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I suppose... I probably will. But I know that won't be the end of it. Because I saw myself. I saw myself draw in the extra energy, take... take Phil, and then pass back into the pipes. 

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] But why does it have to be //you?//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Because he's my brother. And this time I'm going to show up for him.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] But it doesn't make SENSE! Ilse, hold on. Try to shut this thing down. You guys aren't thinking this through rationally. Why would //that// be the loop? Why would you turn yourself into something that would kill your own brother?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Because the packet would have killed him instead, and then it would have blown the whole place sky-high, me included, and as far as anyone would know it would have all been Phil's fault. Instead, something sucked up the effluence in the air, then took him... 

= //<His eyes widen.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I remember thinking he hadn't felt it. That he didn't suffer. Maybe it gave him that. And then it saved the Site, gave my old self the chance to turn the valve, start my penance. Then it disappeared into the system... 

= //<Dr. Deering laughs.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] And you know what? I bet it was still in there back in '43. 2043.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I saw it.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] What?

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I saw it. It leaked down into DePLExA from AAF-D. It tried to kill me, too. On my last run through the cycle.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] That doesn't make sense. You couldn't see it on the video of Phil's acc-- of what happened to Phil.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] But I //could// see it in person when the chronology anchor started to work. When 43 rolled back to reality, it must've been caught in the throes, concretized. It appeared, and it reached out for me...

= //<Silence on recording.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Reached out for you.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Oh my god.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Running in circles for fifteen years, trapped in the pipes, waiting for you to bring me back to life, so I could help you to survive. I like the symmetry.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] This can't be happening.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] At least this time, it really is my idea.

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering sags.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Except you //didn't// help me to survive. You didn't do a //fucking thing// that helped me. 

= //<She laughs.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] God, I should have known it was you.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I'm sorry.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] But you didn't answer my question. Why is this the loop? Phil only died because you did this. If he hadn't died, you never would have decided to do this. The logic doesn't work.

= //<Dr. Deering shrugs.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] It happened, so it does work. The universe requires it to. Bootstrap paradox. Maybe the materials involved... they were ambichronological, remember? Time flowing both ways.

= //<He shrugs again.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Or maybe that's looking too deep. Maybe Phil and I are just predestined to part, like... well.

= //<Chief Torosyan-Deering places a palm on the porthole. Dr. Deering moves to match the gesture, then pulls back.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] That's not enough. It's not universal perversity. It needs to mean something more. You did all of this for him! We both did. All of it. Tell me I'm wrong.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] You're wrong. Half-wrong.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What?

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I never did any of it for him.

= //<Silence on recording.>//

[[span class="ir"]]Dr. Reynders:[[/span]] Two minutes. I'm sorry.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] What about me?

= //<Dr. Deering turns away.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Dougall? What about me? For fuck's sake, let me do it instead. You know that's the better solution.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] No. Absolutely not.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Stop being so selfish!

= //<Dr. Deering looks over his shoulder.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] It's not selfish. It's the least selfish part of this, maybe the only part that isn't. Sure, I'm taking the easy way out. That's who I am. That's all I'm useful for. Maybe I can find a way to do some good in there, however this works out. If I can, I'll keep trying. But I'm weak and lazy and short-sighted, nothing anyone can count on, as you well know. So you need to stay out there, the way you are right now, and keep doing the real work. The good--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] No!

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Yes. Because that's who //you// are, and nobody made you that way but you.

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] No.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Goodbye, Amelia.

= //<Dr. Deering reaches into his labcoat and palms a remote control. He steps into the loading chamber and presses a button on the device. The inner door swings shut.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] I don't forgive you.

= //<A klaxon sounds as the packet delivery system audibly grinds to life.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] Are you listening? I don't forgive you. This isn't how I forgive you.

= //<Dr. Deering looks up, and a flood of material obscures the inner porthole view.>//

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] Just a trick.

= //<MAGIC DRAWER compacts, then delivers its packet.>//

